If I create a FormText widget using its constructor rather than using FormToolkit.createFormText() I get a null pointer exception when I hover over the text. To reproduce take the code below and put it in the ViewPart class for a view.

I realize that this is not how a FormText object was intended to be created but even so I would not expect to see the the NPEs.

public void createPartControl(Composite parent) {
		Composite control = new Composite(parent, SWT.NULL);
		control.setLayout(new TableWrapLayout());
		FormToolkit toolkit = new FormToolkit(parent.getDisplay());
		toolkit.adapt(control);

		FormText upper = new FormText(control, SWT.NULL);
		toolkit.adapt(upper, false, false);
		upper.setText("Hovering the mouse here causes a null pointer exception", false, false);


		Composite separator = toolkit.createCompositeSeparator(control);
	    TableWrapData data = new TableWrapData();
	    data.align = TableWrapData.FILL;
	    data.maxHeight = 1;

	    separator.setLayoutData(data);

		FormText lower = toolkit.createFormText(control, false);
		lower.setText("This text is OK to hover over.", false, false);
	}

